ENTRY            A1518   20260401   20260508   20260508       A134
SUBENT        A1518001   20260401   20260508   20260508       A134
BIB                  6         10
TITLE      A study of the 6Li(alpha,n)9B and 7Li(alpha,n)10B
           reaction
AUTHOR     (M.K.Mehta,W.E.Hunt,H.S.Plendl,R.H.Davis)
INSTITUTE  (1USAFSU)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USAFSU)
REFERENCE  (J,NP,48,90,1963)
HISTORY    (19871029C) Compilation produced by RFNC-VNIIEF Sarov
           (19990323U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20260401A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           Subent 004 was added.
ENDBIB              10
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           13
SUBENT        A1518002   20260401   20260508   20260508       A134
BIB                  9         18
REACTION   (3-LI-7(A,N)5-B-10,,DA)
SAMPLE     (3-LI-7,ENR=0.925) The target was 60 keV 7Li
           evaporated on Ta
MONITOR    (3-LI-7(A,N)5-B-10,,DA)
MONIT-REF  (A1498002,H.Bichsel+,J,PR,108,1025,1957)
DETECTOR   (BF3) Three conventional BF3 counters connected in
           parallel and embedded in a wax filled sheet metal can
           which was positioned 3.8 cm from the target at zero
           degrees with respect to the beam.
COMMENT    From N.Otsuka: First three data points on fig.2 are
           physically incorrect since the 7Li(alpha,n)10B
           threshold energy is ~4.38 MeV.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,M.K.Mehta+,J,NP,48,90,1963) Fig 2
           First three points on fig.2 were deleted from
           the dataset (see COMMENT).
HISTORY    (20260401A) SD: EN-ERR->EN-ERR-DIG, DATA-ERR->ERR-DIG.
           Data were re-digitized. BIB updated.
ENDBIB              18
